cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks and proposes a framework to improve their robustness against adversarial attacks. It may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the defense-attack arms race and proposes a defense mechanism against black-box attacks. Additionally, it involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it evaluates the proposed framework on benchmark datasets. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a framework that intelligently combines unsupervised and supervised learning techniques. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with deep neural networks and their vulnerability to adversarial attacks.
